  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "2012-06-27", 
    "text": "Hire Now Act of 2012 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to: (1) allow certain employers a tax credit for 10% of the excess (if any) of the\u00a0wages and compensation paid to their employees in 2012 over\u00a0the amount of such wages paid in 2011, up to a maximum amount of $5 million; (2) prohibit major integrated oil companies from using the last-in, first-out (LIFO) accounting method; and (3) deny major integrated oil companies a tax deduction for intangible drilling and development costs."
  }, 
